    "In light of the limitations and potential biases of current MT systems, we advocate for continued research and improvements to promote fair and unbiased translations.",
    "Given the multidisciplinary nature of the fields, we advocate for more hybridization both in terms of the technology by, for instance, integrating linguistic information into neural models as in the field itself through more collaboration among (computational) linguists, computer scientists, sociolinguists, ethicists and others.",
    "The remainder of this chapter is organized as follows: Section 2 provides an overview of gender bias in MT and highlights the linguistic settings and statistical dependencies that contribute to its manifestation.",
    "Section 3 presents related work and discusses existing efforts to address gender bias in MT systems.",
    "Section 4 outlines the experiment, including the specific prompts and the analysis."
